This paper deals with the complexity of evaluating conjunctive queries, which is a fundamental problem in database theory. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses parameterized complexity theory, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that studies the complexity of problems with respect to a certain parameter. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions treewidth and pathwidth, which are concepts from graph theory, suggesting that it could belong to cs.DS or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper discusses machine characterizations and complete problems, which are concepts from artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
